.ds n) explain_creat_or_die
.cp 0  \" Solaris defaults to ''.cp 1'', sheesh.
.TH explain_creat_or_die 3
.SH NAME
explain_creat_or_die \- create and open a file creat and report errors
.if require_index \{
.XX "explain_creat_or_die(3)" \
    "create and open a file and report errors"
.\}
.SH SYNOPSIS
#include <libexplain/creat.h>
.sp 0.3
void explain_creat_or_die(const char *pathname, int mode);
.SH DESCRIPTION
The \f[B]explain_creat_or_die\fP function
is used to call the \f[I]creat\fP(2) system
call.  On failure an explanation will be
printed to \f[I]stderr\fP,
obtained from \f[I]explain_creat\fP(3),
and then the process terminates
by calling \f[CW]exit(EXIT_FAILURE)\fP.
.PP
This function is intended to be used in a fashion
similar to the following example:
.RS
.ft CW
.nf
explain_creat_or_die(pathname, mode);
.fi
.ft R
.RE
.TP 8n
\f[I]pathname\fP
The pathname, exactly as to be passed to the \f[I]creat\fP(2) system call.
.TP 8n
\f[I]mode\fP
The mode, exactly as to be passed to the \f[I]creat\fP(2) system call.
.TP 8n
Returns:
This function only returns on success.
On failure, prints an explanation and exits.
.\" ----------------------------------------------------
.SH SEE ALSO
.TP 8n
\f[I]creat\fP(2)
open and possibly create a file or device
